						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken slab leaning on the wall near the Śaṅkaraliṅga temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>11th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record, in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">11th Century A.D.</hi> registers gifts of land, oil-mill and shops. Other details of the gift and the name of the donor are lost. It mentions Seṭṭi Mārajayya.</p>						

